cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with graph similarity and utilizes persistent homology, which is a tool commonly used in computational topology and topological data analysis (TDA). Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which includes TDA, is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with graph visualization and shape mesh datasets, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another likely sub-category. The use of PageRank and bottleneck distance also suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of shape mesh datasets suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
